modules.description: Provides functions to parse and manipulate application binary interface (ABI) specifications, including calling conventions and register mappings. Works with structured data representing function signatures, register sets, and platform-specific ABI rules. Used to extract and validate how functions interface with system calls and hardware registers in low-level program analysis.

Handles ABI recognition and transformation by applying registered passes that modify project structures, such as demangling symbols or registering API-specific actions. Operates on Bap.Std.project data, allowing custom modifications during the ABI phase. Used to inject architecture- or language-specific adjustments before API analysis.
